Awareness around community watch in Mukulya in North Kivu  
• The Beni Sub-coordination, through its communication commission in collaboration with the commune of Bungulu organized in Mukulya in the South-West of Beni in the province of North Kivu a mass sensitization on community watch and on the rise of alerts, as part of the new campaign called "2020, new year without Ebola";  
• To this end, the assistant bourgmestre of the Bungulu commune, Mali Wa Singenda Hamza, congratulated the population in his jurisdiction for his behavior towards teams responding to the EVD and encouraged them to protect health structures; 
• He also explained the risk facing the Mukulya health area, close to the Kalunguta health zone, where Ebola positive cases have been reported in recent days; 
• At the end of this awareness raising, the population of Mukulya undertook to reinforce vigilance strategies around visitors and community engagement in the fight against Ebola; 
• In addition, at Biakato Mines in Ituri, an awareness day was organized on interpersonal communication on vaccination and on the dignified and secure burial protocol (EDS); 
• The fire of screening devices at the Biakato Mines Control Point was also reported on the night of January 2 to 3, 2020 by individuals not otherwise identified.
